history.content:
This class is, academically speaking, absurdly easy. A huge proportion of the class is MEng students from all over the country/world taking their masters units.

You will gain knowledge of how to use some algorithms and libraries that you may have not used before, but the work you do is super trivial. The homework and such is unorganized. It's essentially 1-2 hours of working on a messy Jupyter notebook each week. The homework reminds me of the ML Decal.

I think the primary purpose of this course is the semester-long project you build. The class puts you in touch with startups and some small companies with which you have the option to work on your project. This is the best part of the class.

But how comprehensive are the topics? I have no friend who has taken this course so please write down anything you know(or heard) about this course
